Play area tiles

Click a tile to see the following info:

(x,y)=(25,14)
Q_addr=(x,0xB5)=B519, Q=0x18
ref_addr=(Q,y+0xA0)=AE18
ref=0xBA, udg_page=0x80
udg_addr=(ref,udg_page)=80BA
attr=0x38

where:

  • Q is the 'Q value' for the tile (located at Q_addr)
  • ref is the UDG reference for the tile (located at ref_addr)
  • udg_page is the base page for the tile graphic data (0x80, 0x88, 0x90 or 0x98)
  • udg_addr is the base address of the tile graphic data (ref+0x0100*udg_page)
  • attr is the tile's attribute byte

For an explanation of the Q value and how it is used to determine udg_page and the attribute byte (attr) for a tile, see 606C.

The eight graphic bytes for a tile are located thus:

AddressContents
(ref,udg_page)=udg_addr Graphic byte 1/8
(ref,udg_page+1)=udg_addr+0x0100 Graphic byte 2/8
(ref,udg_page+2)=udg_addr+0x0200 Graphic byte 3/8
(ref,udg_page+3)=udg_addr+0x0300 Graphic byte 4/8
(ref,udg_page+4)=udg_addr+0400 Graphic byte 5/8
(ref,udg_page+5)=udg_addr+0500 Graphic byte 6/8
(ref,udg_page+6)=udg_addr+0600 Graphic byte 7/8
(ref,udg_page+7)=udg_addr+0700 Graphic byte 8/8

Any given tile (identified by udg_addr) may appear at more than one location in the play area.
